He suffered through convalescence to make a bold come back.

First day back on the job and he was capturing the leader of the notorious Mason Kelly Gang. While the act immediately gained him recognition as a top bounty hunter, it also put him in the crosshairs of vengeful outlaws.
The dusty hat that bears the markings of the fight that almost killed him.
The skirmishes became a regular danger to citizens as collateral damage added up.
The more people died, the more he thirsted for blood. His need for revenge was his food, faith, and fire. Nothing outside of it existed.
